{{Infobox journal | title = Urban Education | cover = Urban Education.tif | editor = H. Richard Milner | discipline = [[Education]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Urban Educ. | publisher = [[Sage Publications]] | country = | frequency = Bimonthly | history = 1965-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 2.1 | impact-year = 2017 | website = http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal200963/title | link1 = http://uex.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://uex.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 0042-0859 | eISSN = 1552-8340 | OCLC = 41213228 | LCCN = 64009467 }} '''''Urban Education''''' is a bimonthly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that covers the field of [[Urban studies|urban]] [[education]]. The journal's [[editor-in-chief]] is [[H. Richard Milner, IV|H. Richard Milner]] ([[University of Pittsburgh]]). It was established in 1965 and is published by [[Sage Publications]].
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in [[Scopus]] and the [[Social Sciences Citation Index]]. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', its 2017 [[impact factor]] is 2.1, ranking it 14th out of 40 journals in the category "Urban Studies"<ref name=WoS1>{{cite book |year=2017 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Urban Studies |title=2017 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |work=Web of Science}}</ref> and 49th out of 238 journals in the category "Education & Educational Research".<ref name=WoS2>{{cite book |year=2017 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Education & Educational Research |title=2017 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |work=Web of Science}}</ref>
